      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities use geometry, fluid, and operating conditions sufficiently representative of the COU to support extrapolation of credibility findings.",
      "rationale": "The primary validation activity (Morrison et al. 2022) used the identical FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, bovine blood analog at physiological hematocrit, and pulsatile flow conditions representative of CPB. The secondary velocity-field validation used steady-state PIV on the same geometry; this activity supports turbulence model adequacy but does not cover pulsatile flow structures. The assessment team accepted the combined evidence as sufficient for MRL 2, despite the steady-state mismatch in the secondary activity. This acceptance is the subject of the W-AR-05 weakener documented in this package. Achieved level 2 is claimed but is undermined by the comparator mismatch."
