    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors achieved their required levels under the MRL 2 framework. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping. The primary validation result demonstrates 8.3% normalised RMSE against in-vitro pulsatile hemolysis measurements, within the 10% acceptance criterion. The secondary velocity-field validation against steady-state PIV data was accepted as supplementary evidence for turbulence model adequacy. The assessment team judged the combined evidence sufficient to support the claim that the CFD model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. NOTE: This package contains adversarial weakener W-AR-05 — the primary validation result record omits its comparedAgainst machine-readable link, and the secondary result references a steady-state experimental comparator that is mismatched to the pulsatile COU, constituting a D3 undercutting defeater against the credibility inference.",
